CustomFacts helps to build logic about environment specific configuration
-User can execyte as per the environment configuration [dev/qa/stg/prod]
Steps to create Custom facts-
-Create /etc/ansible/facts.d in Clients machine
-Create one or more custom facts inside facts.d folder
-Output of the facts file should be JSON format
-Facts file should have execution permission

Script:
(ansible-env) root@ip-172-31-17-165:~/ansible-project# cat get_version.fact 
#!/bin/bash

# Get Git Version
if command -v git >/dev/null 2>&1
then
    GIT_VERSION=$(git --version | awk '{print $3}')
else
    GIT_VERSION="not_installed"
fi

# Get Apache Version
if command -v apache2 >/dev/null 2>&1
then
    APACHE_VERSION=$(apache2 -v | head -n 1 | awk -F/ '{print $2}' | awk '{print $1}')
else
    APACHE_VERSION="not_installed"
fi

# Create JSON Output
cat << EOF
{
  "git": "$GIT_VERSION",
  "apache2": "$APACHE_VERSION"
}
EOF

