Why do you need Playbooks?
A Playbook is a YAML file where you define automation tasks step-by-step.
Instead of running commands one by one, playbooks automate everything in sequence.
Write once, use multiple times across environments (Dev, QA, Prod)
Ensures same configuration across all servers
Playbooks allow:

Conditions (when)
Loops
Variables
Roles
Running playbook multiple times gives same result (no duplication)
Infrastructure is defined in code → easy to version control (Git)

