Uses of Set_Fact and Register:
==============================
🔥 1. What is register?
Captures output of a task/module and store it in a variable.
Ansible modules generally returns a data structure
User can store the output of a module using ansible register module.

🔥 2. What is set_fact?
Creates custom variables dynamically
Used to store calculated or modified values
register → output capture
set_fact → custom variable create

- name: Overview of register and set facts
  hosts: all
  become: yes
  remote_user: ubuntu
  tasks:
    - name: Retrieve Installed Shell version
      shell: "bash --version"
      register: bash_version
    - name: Display the variable value
      debug:
        var: bash_version.stdout_lines[0].split()[3]

Output> "bash_version.stdout_lines[0].split()[3]": "5.2.21(1)-release"
Above variable is nooking good so we will go ahead and create a vars?

Beacuse vars is the outside the task. whatever we want to retrive that is not global. That is initialized by inside the task.we should go ahead and mention inside the tasks not outside the tasks.
For that we need to use the set_fact.
- name: Overview of register and set facts
  hosts: all
  become: yes
  remote_user: ubuntu
  tasks:
    - name: Retrieve Installed Shell version
      shell: "bash --version"
      register: bash_version
    - set_fact:
        bash_var: "{{bash_version.stdout_lines[0].split()[3]}}"
    - debug:
        var: bash_var
