Ansible Pause Module -Pause Execution:
======================================
Ansible Pause Module:Pause Module is used to pause the execution of a playbook for a specified amount of time or until a user provides input.
Usecases:
-waiting for a service to start
-waiting for user input
-pausing for manual maintenance
parameters:
===========
minute
seconds
prompt
echo

Example: Totally 3 Scenarios/tags:
1)Example Playbook for pausing for manual maintenance
2)Install and start Apache HTTP sERVER ON uBUNTU
3)Ansible pause parameters

- name: Example playbook for pausing manual ,aintenance
  hosts: all
  become: yes
  remote_user: ubuntu
  tasks:
    - name: Notify about Maintainence
      debug:
        msg: "Maintainence window: Please perform the required checks"
    - name: Pause for maintainence
      pause:
        prompt: "Press 'Enter' to continue after maintainence is completed"
    - name: Resume operations post maintainence
      shell: echo "Mainatinence completed ,resuming operations"
  tags: Scenario1
- name: Install and start Apache HTTP server on ubuntu
  hosts: all
  become: yes
  remote_user: ubuntu
  tasks:
    - name: Update apt package index
      apt:
        update_cache: yes
    - name: Installapache HTTP Server
      apt:
        name: apache2
        state: present
    - name: Start and enable apache service
      systemd:
        name: apache2
        state: started
        enabled: yes
    - name: Pause to allow the webserver to start
      pause:
        seconds: 30
    - name: Ensure apache is running
      systemd:
        name: apache2
        state: started
      register: httpd_status
    - name: Display apache status
      debug:
        msg: "Apache is {{ httpd_status.state }} and enabled"
  tags: Scenario2
- name: Ansible Pause parameters
  hosts: all
  become: yes
  remote_user: ubuntu
  tasks:
    - name: Pause for 30 seconds
      pause:
        seconds: 30
    - name: Pass for user confirmation
      pause: 
        prompt: "press 'Enter' to continue after verifying the backup"
    - name: pause for user input
      pause:
        prompt: "Enter the Username"
        echo: yes
    - name: pause for user password woth out echoing
      pause:
        prompt: "Enter the Password"
        echo: no
  tags: Scenario3

